@node "INFO" "SN NUserTrack v2.3 - Information"
@toc "MAIN"
┌──────────────────────────────────┐
  SN NUserTrack v2.3 - Information
└──────────────────────────────────┘

   Want to show your users (via a bulletin menu-type program or in the
GFiles) who logged on new to your system today?  This utility creates
such a textfile.  This file can then be easily viewed in either of the
two above methods.

Features to note:
  - Multi-line compatible.  You don't have to worry about conflictions.
  - Self-cleaning.  Utilizes no temp files!
  - Looks great when used with SN Bulletin Menu!  :)

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "HISTORY" "SN NUserTrack v2.3 - History"
@toc "MAIN"
┌──────────────────────────────┐
  SN NUserTrack v2.3 - History
└──────────────────────────────┘

  v2.3 - Trimmed it a bit.  Readied it for my latest batch release.
  v2.2 - Cleaned up the code and combined the maintenance routine into
         one program.  Now wears the SN label.
  v2.1 - Bug fix, but never widely released.  Has been in operation for
         over 18 months until I decided tonight it needed a little
         refurbishment.
  v2.0 - First released version.  Served it's purpose, but sometimes
         did some odd things.  Rare skipping of new users.
  v1.0 - 1st generation.  Rudimentary, but operational.

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
